<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,758,1647]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Black and red leafhoppers. Crown yellow, one large black spot on anterior 0.66, one marginal triangular spot laterad of ocelli, black. Face with median round spot dorsally continued as line along median carina, one elongate lateral spot on either side of frontoclypeus and apex of clypellus, black. Anterior marginal transverse band on pronotum shining black, continued laterally as thin line. Forewing red with costal margin, inner claval margin and stripe along middle of corium and apical cells, appendix, black. Legs yellow, hind tibiae dark brown with paler setae. Fore tibiae fuscous, all claws dark brown, metatarsi ventrally dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,758,1647]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Frontoclypeus with ridge-like transverse muscle impressions on either side of median carina. Pronotum transversely finely rugose punctate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,758,1647]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer about as long as height, without ventral process, gradually narrowed caudally, ventral margin oblique and convex. Subgenital plate with inner marginal long macrosetae in addition to dorsal long hairlike setae. Style with well developed heel and toe short and stout, strongly rugose. Aedeagus with well developed extension of atrium, dorsolateral lobe large, pigmented, dorsal connective plate-like, shaft long, slender, curved anteriorly, ventral marginal angular projection absent; gonopore subapical on ventral margin; in posteroventral view ventral extension of atrium appears compressed and together with dorsolateral lobes and shaft looks like a trident. Segment X reaching apex of pygofer, broader proximally than distally.
</paragraph>
